review_blob:
29 years to the day, the Fitz went down.

An excellent porter.  Coffee and chocolate.

Its boldness reminds me of the stormy seas the day she went down.

If you like pounding, this is the beer for you.

I picked up a case for $6.99.  Had a few and immediately drove like a madman back to the store, praying that it didnt sell out before I got back there.  I picked up 6 more cases and have been wasted ever since.

This beer surpasses Olympia Ice as most value for the dollar.

Definate winner of the "Most Bang For Your Buck" Award.
